<font color="#FF0000">WEAPONS PROLIFERATION</font><br>
<tt>Sat Mar 15 19:00:04 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
JJ,<br><br>
Any anger in my comments was totally imagined on your part.  I called you an old man in a spirit of friendly debate, in response to your calling me 'fresh meat'.  I, like you, was careful to say 'No offense' (and I meant it) and I ended my post with a smiley.<br><br>
But you do run the risk of provoking me when you try to say that selling weapons to brutal dicators is in any way justified by the fact that it provides jobs to Americans.  Hell, the Vietnam War provided jobs to Americans, would like to see us start it up again?  Jobs is a common argument pro-weapons folks come up with, silly as it is.  And who *really* gives a shit about whether the weapons manufacturer's life was 'misspent', let's just stop selling weapons to petty third world tyrants.  It is a practice that is totally unjustifiable, so don't even try.<br><br>
Who are these brutal tyrannies that have received  US manufactured weapons?  Turkey, Indonesia, Iraq, Saudi Arabia, Libya, Somalia, to name a few off the top of my head.  Did you see the images of 12 year old Somalia kids running around shooting each other with the good old American M-16 a few years ago on TV?  We sent over American troops to help clean up and our own troops were killed by M16s.  Would you give your kids loaded M-16s to play with?  Then why should we sell them by the 10s of thousands to pettly little unstable countries?  If you hate war, then you can't possibly condone weapons proliferation, jobs and profits or not.
<p><code>-- css@webcom.com  (Chris Schefler) </code><p>


